      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Carey Bloodworth</b>\n</p><p><b>Carey Bloodworth</b>,<br />\nan American senior programmer, veteran <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pi\">Pi</a> programmer, \nand also computer chess programmer \n<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>, \ncomputer chess  historian and collector <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. \nHe worked with <a href=\"/Tony_Marsland\" title=\"Tony Marsland\">Tony Marsland</a> to re-create <a href=\"/Awit\" title=\"Awit\">Awit</a> aka Wita, that it could execute on a <a href=\"/Unix\" title=\"Unix\">Unix</a> box <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>.\nCarey wrote some very fast pi calculation programs, the first one to compute one billion (2^30) decimal digits of pi on a <a href=\"/X86\" title=\"X86\">x86</a> desktop computer in 1999 in less than 9 days \n<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>. \nHis pi calculators also provide tutorials on high-precision and high-performance integer arithmetic \n<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. \nCarey's abandoned  computer chess sites <i>Classic Computer Chess - ... The programs of yesteryear</i> are saved by the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Archive\">Internet Archive</a> \n<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>, \nand are often referred in the <a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Chess Programming Wiki</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#1999\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1999</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Carey_Bloodworth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1999\">1999</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Carey_Bloodworth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 1999\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cecm.sfu.ca/~jborwein/pi_pc.html\">pi_pc.html</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey Bloodworth</a>, June 21, 1999 </li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Carey_Bloodworth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=458105\">\"Sneaky Pete\" program from 1977?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 27, 2005&#160;» <a href=\"/index.php?title=Sneaky_Pete&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Sneaky Pete (page does not exist)\">Sneaky Pete</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=15812\">Update on my Classic Computer Chess programs collection</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 15, 2007</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=16942\">Draw scores</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 05, 2007&#160;» <a href=\"/Draw\" title=\"Draw\">Draw</a>, <a href=\"/Score#DrawScore\" title=\"Score\">Draw Score</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=20451\">Questions about getting ready for multicore programming</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 01, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Parallel_Search\" title=\"Parallel Search\">Parallel Search</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=23562\">31 bit hash values. How often will it fail?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 07, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Transposition_Table#Collisions\" title=\"Transposition Table\">Transposition Table - Collisions</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=216685&amp;t=23616\">Cray Blitz source (Carey)</a> by <a href=\"/Robert_Hyatt\" title=\"Robert Hyatt\">Robert Hyatt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 10, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Cray_Blitz\" title=\"Cray Blitz\">Cray Blitz</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=222228&amp;t=24100\">Re: Two questions for Bob</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 30, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Cartoons\" title=\"Cartoons\">Cartoons</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=225677&amp;t=24419\">Re: chess 7.0</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 16, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Chess_7.0\" title=\"Chess 7.0\">Chess 7.0</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=25546\">Creating EGTBs</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 21, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">Endgame Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=28207\">Bitboards using 2 DOUBLE's&#160;?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 02, 2009&#160;» <a href=\"/Bitboards\" title=\"Bitboards\">Bitboards</a>, <a href=\"/Double\" title=\"Double\">Double</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=30088\">Adapter for non-standard chess engine to Winboard</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 10, 2009&#160;» <a href=\"/Chess_Engine_Communication_Protocol\" title=\"Chess Engine Communication Protocol\">Chess Engine Communication Protocol</a>, <a href=\"/WinBoard\" title=\"WinBoard\">WinBoard</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Carey_Bloodworth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=33305\">What AWIT(y) chess program. Tony Marsland's, that is....</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 17, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Awit\" title=\"Awit\">Awit</a>, <a href=\"/Tony_Marsland\" title=\"Tony Marsland\">Tony Marsland</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=56938&amp;start=2\">Re: Old programs CHAOS and USC</a> by <a href=\"/Dann_Corbit\" title=\"Dann Corbit\">Dann Corbit</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 11, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"/CHAOS\" title=\"CHAOS\">CHAOS</a>, <a href=\"/USC_CP\" title=\"USC CP\">USC CP</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58603\">Antique chess programs</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 15, 2015</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Carey_Bloodworth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20071221115817/http://classicchess.googlepages.com/Chess.htm\">Classic Computer Chess - ... The programs of yesteryear</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey</a> (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Archive\">Internet Archive</a>) <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110723031023/http://www.boo.net/~jasonp/pipage.html\">jasonp's Pi Programs Page</a> (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Archive\">Internet Archive</a>)</li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110723031036/http://www.boo.net/~jasonp/pi-ref.txt\">pi-ref.txt</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey Bloodworth</a>, August 11, 1996</dd>\n<dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110716175634/http://www.boo.net/~jasonp/pi8.c\">pi8.c</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey Bloodworth</a>, September 09, 1996</dd>\n<dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/vonj/snippets.org/blob/master/pi8.c\">snippets/pi8.c at master · vonj/snippets ·  GitHub</a></dd>\n<dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110716175701/http://www.boo.net/~jasonp/pi8.nfo\">pi8.nfo</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Carey Bloodworth</a>, September 27, 1996</dd></dl>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Carey_Bloodworth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\